A man has been arrested on suspicion of raping a 17-year-old girl in a Lancashire town. 
The girl was sexually assaulted twice in Burnley on 29 January, Lancashire Police said.
She was approached near Sainsbury's on Colne Road at about 15:45 GMT and led to Bank Parade and Church Street, the force added.
A 29-year-old man is being held on suspicion of rape and remains in custody for questioning. 
